---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Florida Medical Marijuana Request for Exception (RFE) Guide | Releaf MD" 
  description="Learn how a Request for Exception (RFE) works in Florida, standard daily dosage limits, and the step-by-step process to request higher limits."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-brand-mint py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-brand-primary/10">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center space-y-4">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 bg-brand-primary/10 text-brand-primary rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">
        📋 State Registry Support
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark leading-tight uppercase">Request for Exception (RFE) Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        If standard Florida medical marijuana dosage limits are not meeting your medical needs, we can petition the state for a limit increase.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white border border-brand-primary/10 rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-whisper prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-8">
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark uppercase">What is a Request for Exception (RFE)?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The Florida Office of Medical Marijuana Use (OMMU) enforces standard daily dose and 35/70-day supply limits on all medical cannabis routes of administration. A <strong>Request for Exception (RFE)</strong> is an official clinical petition filed by a qualified physician on your behalf to authorize dosages that exceed these default limits.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          This process is designed for patients who, due to severe conditions, high tolerance, or unique clinical requirements, need higher amounts of THC or smokable flower to manage their qualifying condition.
        </p>

        <!-- Informational Cards -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-brand-mint/40 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-brand-primary/10 flex flex-col justify-between">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif-headline font-bold text-brand-dark text-base mb-2">14-Day Review</h3>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">
                The state OMMU reviews RFE applications within 14 calendar days. If no decision is rendered in this period, the request is automatically approved.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-brand-mint/40 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-brand-primary/10 flex flex-col justify-between">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif-headline font-bold text-brand-dark text-base mb-2">210-Day Validity</h3>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">
                Approved RFEs are tied directly to your active certification cycle and must be renewed every 7 months when your physician orders are updated.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-brand-mint/40 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-brand-primary/10 flex flex-col justify-between">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif-headline font-bold text-brand-dark text-base mb-2">Clinical Rationale</h3>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">
                Requires clinical history, diagnostic records, and a detailed physician justification explaining why standard state limits are insufficient.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark uppercase">Standard Florida Dosage & Supply Limits</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The state enforces default limits on the maximum amount of THC and smokable flower you can purchase in a rolling cycle:
        </p>

        <!-- Limits Table -->
        <div class="overflow-hidden border border-brand-primary/10 rounded-2xl shadow-whisper my-6">
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-slate-200 text-left text-xs">
              <thead class="bg-brand-mint/30">
                <tr>
                  <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark uppercase tracking-wider">Route of Administration</th>
                  <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark uppercase tracking-wider">Daily Limit</th>
                  <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark uppercase tracking-wider">Standard Supply Limit</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100 text-slate-600">
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Smokable Flower</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">2.025 Grams / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">2.5 Ounces (per 35-day period)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Inhalation (Vapes/Concentrates)</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">350 mg THC / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">24,500 mg THC (per 70-day period)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Edibles</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">60 mg THC / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">4,200 mg THC (per 70-day period)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Oral (Capsules/Tinctures)</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">200 mg THC / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">14,000 mg THC (per 70-day period)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Sublingual</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">190 mg THC / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">13,300 mg THC (per 70-day period)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Topical</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">150 mg THC / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">10,500 mg THC (per 70-day period)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-brand-mint/10 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-bold text-brand-dark">Suppository</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3">195 mg THC / Day</td>
                  <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-brand-primary">13,650 mg THC (per 70-day period)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div class="px-5 py-3 bg-brand-mint/10 border-t border-brand-primary/10 text-[10px] text-slate-500">
            <p><strong>Registry Tracking:</strong> Non-smokable routes have a combined aggregate limit of 24,500 mg THC per 70-day cycle. Limits operate on a rolling registry cycle.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark uppercase">How the Exception Request Process Works</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Requesting an exemption is a clinical process integrated directly into your evaluation with Releaf MD:
        </p>

        <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-4 text-slate-600 text-sm">
          <li>
            <strong>Clinical Consultation:</strong> During your consultation with Dr. Kelly Ennix King, discuss your treatment and dosage patterns. If you require higher amounts to manage your symptoms, she will evaluate the medical necessity of an exception.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Evidence Assembly:</strong> Our staff will gather your clinical history, medical records, and diagnostic logs to document why standard limits are insufficient.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Registry Filing:</strong> Dr. Kelly submits the RFE petition electronically through the OMMU Medical Marijuana Use Registry (MMUR).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Registry Update:</strong> Once approved, the state registry instantly adjusts your profile, permitting dispensaries to fill your higher order quantities immediately.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Important Warning Banner -->
        <div class="bg-brand-dark text-white p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-brand-accent my-10 space-y-4">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif-headline text-brand-mint uppercase">Changes and Physician Transfers</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Please note that approved exception requests do not transfer between clinics automatically. If you switch to another certifying physician, your new doctor must evaluate and file a new RFE to re-authorize your higher limit.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark uppercase">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-serif-headline font-bold text-brand-dark text-base">Is an approved exception permanent?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed mt-1">
              No. RFEs are valid only for the duration of your active 210-day certification cycle. At each 30-week renewal visit, your certifying doctor must submit a new RFE to keep the exemption active.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-serif-headline font-bold text-brand-dark text-base">What are the limits while the state reviews my RFE?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed mt-1">
              While the RFE is pending with the Office of Medical Marijuana Use (up to 14 days), your purchasing limits remain capped at the default state quantities.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Footer Actions (Consistent CTA Section) -->
        <div class="border-t border-slate-100 pt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 italic">
            Learn more in our <a href="/florida-medical-marijuana-card-guide" class="text-brand-primary font-bold hover:underline">Complete Florida Card Guide</a>.
          </p>
          <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://live.vcita.com/site/DrKellyKing/online-scheduling" class="bg-brand-accent hover:bg-brand-primary text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-xs uppercase transition-colors shadow-md active-press">
            Request RFE Consultation
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
